I haven’t been in the shop at all to mess with it but my guess is that the problem is with downloading whatever they need to download to parse the new .hoot format.

On the computer that has the issue we first tried to convert the files when connected to the robot so we got the pop up that we needed to connect to the internet the first time we parse the file. On the computer that it works on we never got this pop up.

You might have luck deleting the app and its data then redownloading.

You’ll probably have better luck emailing CTRE support
